    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All three QoIs meet the pre-specified E/uval < 1.96 acceptance criterion. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is acknowledged; the standardized ASTM F1717 protocol constitutes the regulatory reference condition and the gap is considered acceptable for a Class II device with Medium model risk. Validation results generated under ansys-mechanical-2026-q1-build-7-rc2 are considered applicable to the production model version ansys-mechanical-2026-q1-build-7 on the basis of vendor-documented code-freeze equivalence. Overall credibility assessment: Medium assurance level achieved. Submission accepted.",
